If your terminal has "simple" ANSI capability, you will see the following text change as indicated:
        This line should look normal.
        u1This line should be underlined.u0
        o1This line should be bold type.o0
        r1This line should be reverse video.r0

Also, with the use of simple ANSI cursor movement, you should see the word "ANSI" spelled out below.
        >4I<2S<2N<2A

If your terminal has "full" ANSI capability, you will see the word "manhattan" below.  If not, you may see "mantanhat" or some other nonsense.
	mantan<3[3@hat
